-- FACTBOX: Analyst forecasts for July auto sales
-- 
-- Thu Jul 31, 2008 2:59pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/07/31/us-usa-auto-sales-idUSN3048529220080731

 

 (Reuters) - Following is a summary of analyst forecasts for U.S. auto sales in July, based on the seasonally adjusted annualized rate of sales, a widely tracked measure of industry performance known as the SAAR. 

 Automakers are set to release July sales results on Friday. Forecasts range from 13.2 million vehicles to 13.9 million. At the low end of expectations, sales would mark the lowest level since 1993. > * JPMorgan 13.2 million * Global Insight 13.3 million * Citigroup 13.7 million * Goldman Sachs 13.8 million * Lehman Brothers 13.9 million Note: The annualized sales rate for June was 13.6 million units, the weakest monthly result for the industry since August 1993. The U.S. first-half average was 14.5 million units. Total light vehicles sales for 2007 were 16.15 million units. (Reporting by  Soyoung Kim , editing by Leslie Gevirtz)